# Commercial Real Estate Domain

## Property Types

- **Shopping center** — multi-tenant retail (strip, neighborhood, community, power
  center); anchored by grocery/big-box tenants.
- **Retail** — single or small multi-tenant retail buildings.
- **Mixed-use** — combined retail/office/residential.
- **Office** — class A/B/C; measured in rentable square feet (RSF).
- **Industrial** — warehouse, flex, distribution; clear heights, dock doors matter.
- **Pad site / outparcel** — standalone parcel at a center's edge (banks, QSR
  drive-thrus); sold or ground-leased separately.

## Key Concepts

- **Available suite/space** — a leasable unit: suite number, square footage (SF),
  asking rate, space type (inline, endcap, anchor, pad).
- **GLA** — gross leasable area of a property.
- **Asking rate** — usually $/SF/year. **NNN (triple net)** means tenant also pays
  taxes, insurance, CAM; **Gross/FS** means landlord pays. Always display rate type.
- **Anchor tenant** — large traffic-driving tenant (grocer, big-box); co-tenancy with
  anchors is a major selling point.
- **Tenant roster** — current tenants with logos; signals center quality.
- **Traffic counts** — vehicles per day (VPD) on adjacent roads; cite road name, count,
  year, and source.
- **Demographics** — population, households, average household income, daytime
  population, housing values, median age — reported for 1/3/5-mile radii (or drive
  times) around the property.
- **Trade area** — the geographic area a property draws customers from.

## Marketing Outputs

- **Leasing flyer** — 2–8 page PDF: cover, aerial, site plan with availability, demos,
  tenant logos, broker contacts. The workhorse asset.
- **Offering memorandum (OM)** — long-form investment sale package: financials,
  rent roll, market overview.
- **LoopNet / Crexi** — the dominant CRE listing marketplaces; listings need photos,
  aerials, site plans, space-by-space availability data.

## Broker Workflow Reality

Brokers receive engineering site plans (CAD-exported PDFs), trace available spaces,
label SF, add tenant logos, build radius/demo maps, assemble packages, and revise
constantly as spaces lease. Marketing coordinators rebuild the same assets per channel.
This platform exists to eliminate that duplication — see `product-vision.mdc`.

## Display Conventions

- Square footage: `12,500 SF` (comma-separated, "SF" suffix)
- Rates: `$24.00/SF NNN`
- Radii: `1 Mile | 3 Mile | 5 Mile`
- Traffic: `24,500 VPD (2025)`
